            <title>[HIVE-27657] Change hive.fetch.task.conversion.threshold default value</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-27657</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With the introduction of&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/d0a06239b09396d1b7a6414d85011f9a20f8486a/common/src/java/org/apache/hadoop/hive/conf/HiveConf.java#L3532-L3535&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;fetch task caching&lt;/a&gt;, HS2 may quickly run out of memory if there are multiple parallel queries with fetch task.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should be reducing the default value for hive.fetch.task.conversion.threshold to 209715200 (200M) from current 1073741824 (1G)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
